OL,3,CWhat is the government's record on
OL,4,Ctackling Islamophobia?
OL,6,FIn 2024, the Muslim Council of Britain
OL,7,Fsaid Islamophobia in the Conservative
OL,8,FParty was "institutional, tolerated by
OL,9,Fthe leadership and seen as acceptable
OL,10,Fby great swathes of the party
OL,11,Fmembership", after comments by
OL,12,FAnderson and Braverman.
OL,14,FDefining "Islamophobia"
OL,16,FFor years, there have been disputes
OL,17,Fover exactly how to define
OL,18,FIslamaphobia, with the Conservatives
OL,19,Fusing a different definition to the
OL,20,Fone used by other parties and over 750
OL,21,FBritish Muslim organisations.
